I"‡<p>School-based education validates through <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/recontextualizing-educational-resources-enables-a-litmus-test-for-credentialism">credentials</a>. However, in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/creative-output-can-support-educational-input-in-free-learning">free learning</a>, validation can be done by means of the actual value of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/creative-output-can-support-educational-input-in-free-learning">creative output</a>. In this, credentials become a meaningless <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/written-word-is-a-proxy-for-thought">proxy</a>.</p>
